        {
            "name": "Metal Forms",
            "type": "section",
            "text": "Though metal elementals are made almost entirely of metal, most are composed of layers of different metals in tiny fragments, as complex as a body of flesh or plant matter. Many of these metals are rusted or decayed from the natural, slow entropy of the Plane of Metal.",
            "sources": [
